dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.05ecc976-ac54-463e-b322-6357f5d81138.description=Allows a user to select how they should be notified of the outcome of a flow, and shows them a message in that way. Inputs\: notifydata - The message to notify the user of. notifyMethod - The method of notification (file, email, display). subject - This is a description of what the notification is about. destination - for files, the file to write to, for emails the email to send to. notificationServer - If the specified method send the notifyData to a server, this is the name of the server to notify (i.e. an email server) from - This is the originator of the message (email from address). sourceServer - Some integrations use a multi-level server architecture for processin tickets, this is the name of a mid-tier server in such an architecture. serverPort - The port the service to notify on the server is running on. username - A username to use when authenticating to a notification method requireing authentication. password - The password for username. Responses\: success - The user was notified. failure - Notification failed. dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.0cba4013-aa3d-4f01-8e40-4de7494d4961.prompt=Notification option\: dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.11928186-5f9e-49ea-81f3-1dfaf9053609.transition.description=Unable to compute difference between ping times. dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.1a92cae8-0e3d-4729-9934-a24b2d7cc8de.description= Checks if a threshold matches a measuredValue and creates a diagnostic summary if they do not. inputs\: measuredValue - value measured. threshold - A threshold to compare the measuredValue against.. Threshold function - (\=\=, \!\=, >, >\=, <, <\=) the type of threshold diagnostic name - the name of this diagnostic. diagnostic so far - The output of previous diagnostics, used for chaining diagnostics together. recommended resolution - A reccomendation for resolving the problem if the measured value is outside the threshold. responses\: success - sublist is contained in container. dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.2039ac94-eb39-4bb1-96fc-696e06b1c961.description=
Pings the requested machine from a remote host

Input Parameters\:
host - hostname or IP address of the host to ping from.
username - The username to use to authenticate to host.
password - The password to use to authenticate to host.
target - The target server to ping.
packets - The number of packets to send to target.
packetSize - The size of packets to send to target.

Responses\:
passed - a successful connection was made
failure - target did not respond to ping.
Connection Error - Unable to connect to host.
Unknown Target - could not resolve target to a valid IP address

Extra Results\:
output - raw output of the results
address - actual IP address pinged
% Packet Loss - The percentage of packets that ping replies were received for.
average latency - The average ping response time in milliseconds.
max latency - The maximum response time of all the pings (in milliseconds).
min latency - the minimum number of milliseconds it took to receive a ping response.
dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.2be8a949-afd3-47cc-b616-df4a2adc025a.description=Iterates through a list of values. Inputs\: list - The list to iterate through. separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the list. Returns\: The current element of the list, if the response is has more Responses\: has more - Another value was in the list, and has been returned. has no more - The iterator has gone fully through the list. This response will only be returned once per iteration through the list, a subsequent call to the Iterator will restart the Iteration through the list. failure - failed to process the list. Note\: Where the iterator is in the list is tracked by each step's unique id. Therefore you can iterate on the same list from multiple steps simultaneously. WARNING\: Any step that will use the results of this Iterator operation will, by default, attempt to assign that step's inputs from a flow variable. If this is left checked, then the first element of the iterator will be used for every cycle of iteration. dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.2f03796b-6951-49af-bc8b-acfcec0ef09f.prompt=Notification option\: dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.45892c71-2985-4004-8c07-5d0325743431.description=
Useful Op to keep a running results.
Takes a string input (resultText) and appends this to a global context key of "runningResults".

Input Parameters\:
keyName - name of context key to append to
resultText - string input to append
delimiter - (leave blank for none) the delimiter to put between what is already in keyName before appending resultText

Responses\:
success - assigned the context variable

Context\:
runningResults

Scriptlet Example\:
currentResults \= scriptletContext.get("runningResults");

if (currentResults \=\= null) {
   currentResults \= resultText;
} else {
   currentResults +\= resultText;
}


scriptletContext.putGlobal("runningResults", currentResults);
dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.5c696f20-2afd-44cb-ac3e-25b40d62810a.description=
Computes a mathematical operation.

Input Parameters\:
value1 - the first value
value2 - the second value
operator - operation to perform (+,-,*,/,%);

Responses\:
success - the expression was evaluated.
failure - the expression could not be evaluated.

Returns\: the value of the expression.

dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.dd1b7aff-2716-4561-968f-778be4915da4.prompt=Enter a value for host dfbcb2e8-f156-4f5f-a2c8-ea71d6fa9307.description=
This flow uses a trace route to attempt to localize a network failure.

Note\: if a route cannot be found, it will take a long time to enumerate each hop. If this happens at the beginning of the trace route, the trace route may time out with a 500 server error. In this case, decrease the maxhops count.

inputs\:
host - The host to traceroute from.
username - credentials for host.
password - credentials for host.
target - The host to traceroute to.
hopTimeThreshold - The maximum amount of acceptable time between hops.
maxhops - The maximum number of hops to traceroute over.
diagnostic so far - The diagnostic so far, used for chaining diagnostics.
notifyMethod - How the user should be informed of the diagnostic's output.

Responses\:
success - The operation was successful.
failure - something went wrong.

Returns\:
A human readable diagnostic (updated diagnostic so far)

flow.name: TraceRoute Diagnostic

staticBinding.value: Traceroute long hop check for node ${address}

A route could not be found to ${target} from ${host}. The last server on the traced route was ${lastAddress}. The recommended procedure for resolving this issue is: Ensure ${lastAddress} has a route to ${target}. Or change the routing table on a hop before ${lastAddress} to use a different route to ${host}.
Here is your traceroute diagnostic for ${target}
